CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 13, 1965, pg. 24, reads: "Victory Ride - Schenley High School Coach Willard Fisher is lifted to the shoulders of his victorious players just after they had clinched the city high school basketball championship by defeating South Hills, last week. It is Schenley's first city title in 23 years. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Members of Schenley High School basketball team lifting up Coach Willard Fisher, after clinching championship title in University of Pittsburgh Field House
